channel.title: Ok!
channel.description: Well, I fixed my internet. I was using my neighbors router :D So I'm trying to get into the router and I tried the password that I used before for the same router, and It doesnt work. Does anybody know how to find out you're router password? I already tried to restart my router, but It didnt reset the password.

item.title: Ok!
item.dc:creator: @sickedank sickedank
item.description:
@sickedank wrote:

if the password doesn’t work, you can reset your router on your own.

In the back or maybe on the side of the router, there should be a button that instead of popping out, is a hole. You have to stick a needle or pen of some sort to press it. You should hold it for about 30 seconds. Then, the router will be reset and you will be able to set a new password for the router.

Read full topic
